commText: Kohli and du Plessis are at the crease. Kohli is on strike. Abhishek Sharma will open the attack
Abhishek Sharma to Kohli, 1 run, full delivery on the stumps, Kohli flicks to mid-on

Abhishek Sharma to du Plessis, FOUR, outside edge and flies for four! Look at the amount of turn Abhishek Sharma got despite bowling with the new ball. Faf wanted to cut, thick edge escapes through the vacant slip region and short third man was very wide
Abhishek Sharma to du Plessis, no run, blocked
Abhishek Sharma to du Plessis, 1 run, fullish and swinging back in, Faf manages to work it to mid-on

Abhishek Sharma to Kohli, no run, dropped! Abhishek Sharma wasn't expecting this to come to him at all. Was a simple chance though. Shortish delivery turning away, Virat couldn't control the pull, sliced it straighter than he wanted to, Abhishek Sharma was late to stick his right hand out and it didn't stick
Abhishek Sharma to Kohli, FOUR, good adjustment from Virat to react to the inswinger that cramped him on the pull and placed it to the right of deep mid-wicket to get going
Bhuvneshwar Kumar, right-arm fast medium, comes into the attack
Bhuvneshwar to du Plessis, 1 run, short of length delivery on the leg stump, Faf glances it to backward square leg
Bhuvneshwar to Kohli, no run, short of length delivery outside off stump, Kohli dabs towards point
Bhuvneshwar to Kohli, no run, Bhuvi is already taking pace off! Slower delivery outside off stump, Virat advances to play a big shot and gets beaten
Bhuvneshwar to Kohli, FOUR, edgedddd and just over short third man. The scrambled seam short of length delivery outside off stump, Kohli slashes hard and gets a thick edge that escapes for four
Bhuvneshwar to Kohli, SIX, oh what a flick that is from Virat! Full and on the pads, but the power he generated with those rubber wrists for a flat hit over square is unbelievable
Bhuvneshwar to Kohli, no run, fullish delivery outside off stump, Virat pushes it to the off-side
More left arm spin to both these batters
Shahbaz Ahmed, Left arm orthodox, comes into the attack

Shahbaz Ahmed to du Plessis, FOUR, Faf escapes another outside edge and it goes to third man. Flighted delivery outside off stump, Faf swings hard and gets lucky. Cummins liked what he saw from the bowler and claps for him
Shahbaz Ahmed to du Plessis, no run, pushed to the off-side

Shahbaz Ahmed to du Plessis, SIX, that's a muscular inside out lofted drive over long-off. Full and outside off stump, Faf steps out and gets to the pitch of the ball and plays a get out of my sight shot for six
Shahbaz Ahmed to du Plessis, 1 run, slapped to deep extra-cover

Shahbaz Ahmed to Kohli, 1 run, oh escapes a runout! Virat cut this to point, diving effort but Faf was already at his end, Virat took off very late but the bowler wasn't near the stumps to collect the throw properly

Shahbaz Ahmed to du Plessis, SIX, oh ho ho! That's a proper agricultural slog if ever there was one. Shahbaz Ahmed dropped it short on seeing the batter step out but Faf decided I'm having this no different and went through with the slog. Had to lower the bat swing to pick that ball up and it flew flat and landed on the cushion
Bhuvneshwar to Kohli, FOUR, calculated pull shot wide of mid-on! Short of a length delivery, Virat just tried to place that ball than hit it hard and he gets four

Bhuvneshwar to Kohli, FOUR, edgeee over short third man again! That's the fourth boundary RCB have got in that direction. Short of a length delivery outside off stump, Virat swings hard, thick edge and RCB have got the start to spice this contest up
Stat: 512* sixes from the first 30* matches in IPL 2024 so far - already crossed the final tally from the 2009 edition (506 in 57 games)
Bhuvneshwar to Kohli, 1 run, short of length delivery, Virat taps it to cover and says over to you mate, Faf!
Bhuvneshwar to du Plessis, no run, oh beaten! Could have easily been a drag on. Seems like it cut back in off the seam from short of length to surprise Faf on the slog

Bhuvneshwar to du Plessis, FOUR, Faf is not going to stop himself from trying the slog every ball. The target demands such play anyway. Knuckle ball into the wicket, Faf drags it wide of mid-wicket and its four more

Bhuvneshwar to du Plessis, FOUR, looks like they are in the mood to better what SRH did in the powerplay! Short of a length delivery, Faf drags the short of length delivery wide of mid-wicket and the boundaries are bleeding
T Natarajan, left-arm fast medium, comes into the attack
T Natarajan to Kohli, 1 run, short of length delivery on the stumps, Virat slogs and mistimes to deep square leg
T Natarajan to du Plessis, 1 run, he's ready for a big hit every ball with a high back lift, but SRH have a man stationed at deep mid and Natarajan is bowling to the field. Just one

T Natarajan to Kohli, FOUR, in the airrr, sliced over point. Shahbaz runs back, can't get the catch but he doesn't put int he dive too! Pace off from Nattu, Virat nicely slices it with an open bat face and manages to get it over the infield

T Natarajan to Kohli, no run, oh yorked himself and almost lost the leg stump! Full credit to Nattu for targetting the yorker despite seeing the batter advance. Virat had nowhere to hide, the bat wasn't even close and somehow it missed the leg stump
T Natarajan to Kohli, 2 runs, jumps down the pitch and mishits another one, Markram runs back from mid-off but can't get the catch. Two more

T Natarajan to Kohli, SIX, full toss on the pads and whipped away over mid-wicket for six. This guy has some power in those wrists. Nattu bowled a good over until this point, but Virat expertly put the loose ball away to win the over for RCB
Pat Cummins, right-arm fast, comes into the attack
Cummins to du Plessis, no run, oh off the pad and rolls to the keeper. Faf didn't know where this ball went. Was full and fast on the pads, he swung and missed

Cummins to du Plessis, FOUR, smacked down the ground! "Come onnn" says Virat from the other end. Sure was some shot to get that excitement going. Length delivery from Cummins, Faf stays leg-side and smacks it down the ground

Cummins to du Plessis, no run, oh dear, he's hit close the box! And he feels the pain. Shares a smile and sees the funny side of it late though. Got inside the line to try and whip this behind square but Cummins rushed him for pace with a short of length delivery
Cummins to du Plessis, 1 run, complete mistimed pull to mid-off as Cummins rushes Faf again with a short of length delivery

Cummins to Kohli, no run, that's the third time in the over that Cummins has forced the batters to miss the attempted whip behind square and hit the pad or body. Looks like Cummins cramping the batters for room is doing it for him
Cummins to Kohli, FOUR, Virat backs away knowing what Cummins is going do to - bowl into him - and smashes this down the ground for four over the non-striker's end

Over Summary (1-6): -- Kohli is dropped by Sharma on a duck -- Shahbaz disappears for 18 in his first over -- Bhuvi goes for 17 in his second over -- RCB bring up their fifty inside the 4th over -- RCB score 79 in the powerplay
RCB have bettered SRH's PP score by 3 runs
Highest Powerplay totals for RCB (IPL) 79/0 vs SRH Bengaluru 2024 * 79/1 vs KTK Bengaluru 2011 75/2 vs CSK Bengaluru 2023 70/1 vs PK Bengaluru 2019
Mayank Markande, right-arm leg break, comes into the attack
Markande to du Plessis, 1 run, flatter on the leg stump, Faf punches it to long-off
Markande to Kohli, THATS OUT!! Bowled!!

Markande to Kohli, out Bowled!! Virat being castled with a googly by a leggie! And how bold of Markande to slow it up to these batters and tease the big hit. Virat misses the slog-sweep, deceived in flight and the ball hits middle and leg. Markande absolutely roars and why not, he's outsmarted one of the best in the world. Cummins is very happy for his teammate and SRH have got the opening they were badly looking for. End of great entertainment from Virat. But he's livid with himself and smashes the bat onto his pad as he walks off. Just misread the line too. Was too outside the line and tried to fetch the shot. Kohli b Markande 42(20) [4s-6 6s-2]
Will Jacks, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Markande to Will Jacks, 1 run, flatter delivery on the leg stump, Jacks punches it to long-on
Markande to du Plessis, 1 run, shortish again, Faf works it to long-on
Markande to Will Jacks, 1 run, googly outside off stump, Jacks drags the slog to backward square leg off the inside edge
Markande to du Plessis, 1 run, shortish and slow outside off stump, Faf reaches out to slap it to long-off. Just 5 off that over
Jaydev Unadkat, left-arm fast medium, comes into the attack
Here is Unadkat.

Unadkat to du Plessis, SIX, starts with a short ball at 130.1 kph delivery and du Plessis has slammed it over deep backward square for a sixer. Woeful delivery and du Plessis put it away with elan. He needs to bowl it into the deck but not at that height for sure

Unadkat to du Plessis, 1 run, lovely cutter at 107.1 kph from a back of a length spot. du Plessis stabs it down into the off-side for a single. The ball sprang up pn the batter who almost fended it off into the off-side. Only a run

Unadkat to Will Jacks, FOUR, slower one, at 110.3 kph. Will Jacks looks to pull, makes contact little early and the edge goes fine to the left of the keeper and the man at long leg had no chance. 11 off 3 balls so far
And the umpire calls it a dead ball. Someone decided to take a stroll near the sight-screen. Ignorance isn't bliss, always!
Unadkat to Will Jacks, 1 run, length delivery, well outside off, Will Jacks cue-ends it down into the off-side for a single

Unadkat to du Plessis, FOUR, slower, one, outside off, at 105.9 kph. du Plessis slices it by reaching out for it and sends it over point. Lovely shot by du Plessis and he gets to fifty! He has reached his 50 off 23 balls. Has been a good knock so far from the skipper. Needs to carry on for long
Unadkat to du Plessis, THATS OUT!! Run Out!!

Unadkat to du Plessis, out Will Jacks Run Out!! That's tragedy for RCB. Unadkat did well to get a fair bit of hand on it. Another slower delivery, well outside off and du Plessis slammed it off the inner-half off the bat and back at the bowler. Unadkat got his right palm on it and the ball ricocheted on to the sticks. The deflection was so noticeable that the on-field umpire gave Jacks out. Sad way to get out. RCB would be gutted. Will Jacks run out (Unadkat) 7(4) [4s-1]
Rajat Patidar, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Markande to Rajat Patidar, 1 run, goes back and nudges it down on to the on-side for a single
Markande to du Plessis, 1 run, heaves it down to deep mid for a single as that was a googly and followed the batter
Markande to Rajat Patidar, no run, flatter one, outside off, dabbed down to short third man

Markande to Rajat Patidar, SIX, straight down the ground for a sixer. Was a length delivery, Rajat Patidar stayed on the back foot and slammed it well over the bowler's head for a sixer. Massive hit indeed as he generated a good bat swing
Markande to Rajat Patidar, wide, tossed up delivery, well outside off, left alone and has been wided
Markande to Rajat Patidar, 2 runs, 89.3 kph, Rajat Patidar flogs it sans much timing and the man at long-on cuts it off. They get a brace
Markande to Rajat Patidar, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Markande to Rajat Patidar, out Caught by Nitish Reddy!! The googly does it again. Was a floaty googly, Rajat Patidar went for the swipe by backing away a little. He didn't get much distance on it and the man at deep mid cupped it easy. Third wicket in three overs for SRH. Patidar needed to carry on as the rate is not going to come down but fails. Rajat Patidar c Nitish Reddy b Markande 9(5) [6s-1]
Saurav Chauhan, left handed bat, comes to the crease
Pat Cummins [1.0-0-9-0] is back into the attack
Cummins to du Plessis, FOUR, not a bad ball but put away! Cramped the batter for room. du Plessis pulled it wide of long leg for a four
Cummins to du Plessis, SIX, wow! That's huge. Length delivery angling in, du Plessis backed away and nonchalantly whipped it off the pads for a sixer. Huge hit indeed. He is looking really good
Cummins to du Plessis, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Cummins to du Plessis, out Caught by Klaasen!! The cutter has done it. The short ball dug in, du Plessis looked to hook it but the extra bounce and the lack of pace has done it. Another one falls. They are going down like a lead balloon here. The batter was a little early into the short. Infact, the square leg umpire was about to call it a wide but the batter managed to get a feather on it. The onfield umpire though picked up the edge. End of a superb knock. du Plessis c Klaasen b Cummins 62(28) [4s-7 6s-4]

Has DK edged it down leg? An appeal has been made for a strangle down leg. SRH lose a review. That was a back of a length delivery delivery down leg and hit the thigh pad on the way to make the noise and create the confusion.
Dinesh Karthik, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Cummins to Karthik, no run, Cummins went up and so did Klaasen but DK never looked bothered. They went up for the review but that has been lost. Hit the thigh pad on its way to the keeper
Cummins to Karthik, 1 run, solid forward push into the off-side and Karthik is off the mark
Cummins to Saurav Chauhan, THATS OUT!! Lbw!!

Cummins to Saurav Chauhan, out Lbw!! Superb yorker to the newbie and Saurav Chauhan fails to wood it. He is gone. Beaten by pace. Lock, stock, barrel. Went round the wicket and speared in the yorker. Saurav Chauhan failed to get bat on it and the finger went up. Half the side is gone. Cummins magic continues. Got rid of Faf and now Chauhan. Saurav Chauhan lbw b Cummins 0(1)
Mahipal Lomror, left handed bat, comes to the crease
Markande to Karthik, no run, stabs it down to cover
Markande to Karthik, 1 run, sits down, fetches it from outside off and sweeps it down to deep square for a single
Another review. Lomror went for the slog sweep and missed. Was a fuller ball, Lomror sat down to slog sweep and missed the line. Was a googly and it is umpire's call on hitting. Review retained.

Markande to Lomror, no run, was a tossed up delivery, googly, Lomror went for the slog sweep and missed. The googly dipped and was too full as well. Lomror was lucky that he wasn't given out as it was umpire's call on hitting
Markande to Lomror, wide, well tossed up, outside off, left alone and has been wided
Markande to Lomror, 1 run, flogs that down to deep mid for a single as that was a tossed up delivery
Markande to Karthik, 1 run, and sweeps it down to deep mid for a single
Markande to Lomror, 1 run, slaps it down to deep cover for a single as that was a tossed up delivery outside off
T Natarajan [1.0-0-14-0] is back into the attack
T Natarajan to Lomror, 1 run, angles in, at 132 kph, Lomror tucks it down to deep mid for a single
T Natarajan to Karthik, wide, banged in short at 126.9 kph, well over the batter, left alone and has been wided
T Natarajan to Karthik, 1 run, length delivery at 132.6 kph. Karthik flogs that wide of mid-wicket sans any timing for a single
T Natarajan to Lomror, wide, banged in, Lomror lets it go to the keeper for a wide as that was too short
T Natarajan to Lomror, wide, very full, down leg, Lomror misses the clip and has been wided
T Natarajan to Lomror, 1 run, slices a short of length delivery at 137.7 kph over the bowler for a single. The man at mid-off cut it off to his left. Didn't time it as the batter was cramped for room
T Natarajan to Karthik, no run, slower one, angled across at 120.7 kph. Karthik looked to slash at it and misses
T Natarajan to Karthik, 1 run, fuller length delivery, outside off, Karthik blasts it through the off-side for a single
T Natarajan to Lomror, 1 run, fuller length delivery, outside off, Lomror blasts it down to long-off for a single

Over Summary (7-12): -- Brave Markande tosses a googly up and knocks over Kohli -- Jacks runout in unlucky fashion -- Markande removes Patidar too -- Double dent from Cummins as he gets Faf and Saurav is same over -- Markande almost traps Lomror LBW, ump's call saves batter
Markande to Lomror, SIX, tossed up delivery, at 95.8 kph. Lomror almost sliced it but managed to get a lot of bat on it and went over the leaping fielder at long-off. Six but too late?
Markande to Lomror, SIX, well tossed up delivery at 84.1 kph. Lomror sits down and hits it flat. That went flying into the deep mid cushion for a sixer. Was well hit and into the gap
Markande to Lomror, 1 run, goes back and slashes it down to deep cover for a single

Markande to Karthik, SIX, slips out of the hand of the bowler and DK has slammed it over long leg. Got under it and hit it high and handsome over the fence. Massive hit as 19 have come off the over already
Markande to Karthik, wide, well doled up delivery, well wide outside off and has been left alone for it to be wided
Markande to Karthik, FOUR, 84.6 kph. Karthik has reverse slapped it over point. That was dropped a little short abd Karthik hit it very well
Markande to Karthik, 1 run, goes back and slaps it down to long-on for a single
Jaydev Unadkat [1.0-0-16-0] is back into the attack
Unadkat to Karthik, FOUR, slower one, outside off, Karthik slices it over point for a four. That was well placed

Unadkat to Karthik, FOUR, DK show is on. Slower, well outside off and Karthik sits back to slap it over cover. One bounce and into the fence. Unadkat is being taken to the cleaners here. 120 off 40 balls now
Unadkat to Karthik, 1 run, length delivery, outside off, stabbed out into the off-side for a single. He has moved to 25 off 14 balls
Unadkat to Lomror, 1 run, slower short ball, at 112.1 kph, Lomror mistimes the pull down to deep mid for a single. The ball sat into the deck and the batter never had any momentum while playing that

Unadkat to Karthik, SIX, he has picked the bones out of that dead meat of a delivery. Slower one at 95 kph, well outside off. Karthik sat down and slammed the slog sweep wide of long-on for a sixer. He is timing them so well
Unadkat to Karthik, wide, spinning slower delivery at 111.9 kph. Was well wide outside off and Karthik left it alone for it to be wided

Unadkat to Karthik, FOUR, goes full, goes quick at 131.7 kph. Karthik stays low, goes on his knees and paddles it over short fine. This man is certainly making a case now for the T20 WC. Superb balance at the crease and he is watching the ball like a football. 21 off the over. 46 off the last two overs
Pat Cummins [2.0-0-20-2] is back into the attack
Cummins to Lomror, THATS OUT!! Bowled!!

Cummins to Lomror, out Bowled!! Back of a length delivery at 120.6 kph. Lomror looked to slash at it and got it off the inside edge to drag it on to the sticks. Third strike for Cummins in this game. He seems to have carried a deck with himself from Australia. The batter was cramped for room and that didn't help him. They needed a wicket and their skipper has delivered. He is on a hat-trick. Lomror b Cummins 19(11) [6s-2]
Anuj Rawat, left handed bat, comes to the crease
Cummins to Anuj Rawat, no run, fuller ball, at the sticks, whipped back to the bowler
Cummins to Anuj Rawat, 1 run, slower one at 115 kph. Anuj Rawat stabbed it down wide of point for a single
Cummins to Karthik, 1 run, slower short ball at 121.3 kph, Karthik mistimes the pull down to long leg as he was cramped for room
Cummins to Anuj Rawat, no run, top over from a top player! Short, angled across, slashed down to point. Only two off the over
Cummins to Anuj Rawat, FOUR, hits it on top of the bounce and slams it wide of point for a four. Was another slower delivery, well wide outside off and Anuj Rawat got the room to free his arms

Time-out. RCB need 101 in 5 overs. The game frankly has been out of their reach ever since they lost Kohli and a few others in succession. But they would want to bridge the gap as it will ensure their NRR isn't hurt that much. They were actually out-batted when SRH scored 287. But Faf, Kohli and DK have done well to ensure that the game has had some interest in it.
T Natarajan [2.0-0-22-0] is back into the attack
T Natarajan to Karthik, SIX, that has landed in Kormangala! Fetch that says DK. Fuller on the pads, Karthik kept his balance and slammed it off the pads for a 108m hit. Astounding hit from the batter
T Natarajan to Karthik, 2 runs, superb riposte from the bowler. Nails the yorker but the diligent DK nudged it down to deep mid for a couple of runs
T Natarajan to Karthik, no run, slower short ball, Karthik fails to wood it as the ball stuck into the deck a little
DK has reviewed a wide. Has been wided by the third umpire. Umpire Anil Chaudhary has been asked to reverse it.
T Natarajan to Karthik, wide, fuller, angled across, was on the tramline actually and ump didn't call it. But the third umpire was called in as DK reviewed it. Got the wide
T Natarajan to Karthik, 1 run, fuller length delivery, slices it over point. They get a single
T Natarajan to Anuj Rawat, byes, 1 run, slower, shorter. Anuj Rawat looks to slash and misses. The keeper fumbles and they steal a bye
T Natarajan to Karthik, 1 run, low full toss at 131.7 kph. Karthik slices it down to deep cover for a single. 89 needed off 24 balls. The onus on DK to bring down the margin for RCB
Over Summary (12-16): -- DK-Lomror smack Markande for 25 in an over -- DK on a rampage as Unadkat taken for 21 runs -- Cummins puts the brakes by knock over Lomror -- DK hits a 108m six
Cummins will bowl out here.

Cummins to Karthik, SIX, fifty off 23 balls. Cricket commentator for most part of the year and then comes here and has sizzled for most times he has come out to bat. Was a short ball, into the deck, slammed over deep mid
Cummins to Karthik, 2 runs, slower short ball, mistimed the pull down to deep mid for a couple more
Cummins to Karthik, no run, slower, wider, slapped down to mid-off and they don't take a single
Cummins to Karthik, 1 run, into the deck, slower, shorter, Karthik pulls it hard but finds deep mid. Only a single. 80 needed off 20 balls
Cummins to Anuj Rawat, 1 run, slower, fuller, at 116.4 kph, Anuj Rawat drills the drive down to long-off for a single
Cummins to Karthik, wide, too short, at 125.6 kph. Karthik lets it go and has been wided

Cummins to Karthik, SIX, he is using his bat like a bazooka! Short, slower, Karthik slammed the pull and sent it over deep backward square for a sixer. Amazing strokeplay from the veteran. 72 needed off 18 balls now. That's 12 sixes!
Bhuvneshwar Kumar [2.0-0-28-0] is back into the attack
Bhuvneshwar to Anuj Rawat, wide, starts with a wide well outside off. Slower delivery as well. Anuj Rawat saw it and left it alone
Bhuvneshwar to Anuj Rawat, no run, back of a length delivery, angled across, Anuj Rawat looked to slash it and misses. Extra bounce on it
Bhuvi wasn't sure but they have decided to review it. Was slower, fuller, Anuj Rawat has edged it on to his pads. SRH lose all their reviews. Klaasen didn't want his skipper to review it.
Bhuvneshwar to Anuj Rawat, 1 run, fuller ball, right up there, Anuj Rawat managed to cue-end it on to his pads. There was an appeal by the bowler and they decided to review it
Bhuvneshwar to Karthik, 1 run, right up there, Karthik has squeezed it down to short third man for a single
Bhuvneshwar to Anuj Rawat, 1 run, slower, shorter, Anuj Rawat stays back and slaps it down to deep cover for a single
Bhuvneshwar to Karthik, wide, slower, shorter, outside off and Karthik initially wanted to scoop it but that was too wide outside off
Bhuvneshwar to Karthik, wide, length delivery, well wide outside off and left alone for it to be wided. 66 needed off 14 balls. Only if RCB would have wboled a little better
Bhuvneshwar to Karthik, SIX, is this a spinner Mr. DK? Switches his grip and has reverse slapped it over point for a sixer. Superb hit indeed
Bhuvneshwar to Karthik, wide, slower, wide, left alone and has been wided
Bhuvneshwar to Karthik, 1 run, nails the yorker and Karthik jams it down to deep cover for a single. 58 needed off 12 balls
T Natarajan [3.0-0-33-0] is back into the attack
T Natarajan to Karthik, SIX, he wants to bring the roof down for sure. Natarajan misses his mark and Karthik thumps it over deep mid. This is manic hitting indeed from DK

T Natarajan to Karthik, 2 runs, and Phillips almost plucked out a stunner. He is known to pluck out stunners. Was a fuller ball. Karthik whipped it, the ball was dipping on the fielder who dived forward. Two more to the tally
T Natarajan to Karthik, FOUR, length delivery angled across, reverse shovelled and just wide of the keeper for a four. 46 needed off 9 balls
T Natarajan to Karthik, 2 runs, very full from round the wicket and has been whipped wide of long-on for a brace. 44 needed now off 8 balls
T Natarajan to Karthik, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

T Natarajan to Karthik, out Caught by Klaasen!! End of a breathtaking knock from DK. This loss could have been worse for RCB but he managed to hang in there with some style and panache. He batted like a genius but has to go now. Was a fuller ball, outside off, Karthik wanted to slap it but edged it to the keeper. Simple take for Klaasen. Karthik c Klaasen b T Natarajan 83(35) [4s-5 6s-7]
Vijaykumar Vyshak, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Stat: 7 x 50+ partnerships in this match - there haven't been more than five in any T20 match previously
T Natarajan to Vijaykumar Vyshak, no run, right up there, Vijaykumar Vyshak digs it out into the off-side and Anuj Rawat rejects the plea for a single
Bhuvneshwar to Anuj Rawat, FOUR, good delivery, fuller at 137 kph. Excellent reply as he opened the face of the bat and played it fine for a four
Bhuvneshwar to Anuj Rawat, FOUR, low full toss, outside off, sliced over short third man for a four. Wanted to heave it across the line but got an edge on it to send it away
Bhuvneshwar to Anuj Rawat, 1 run, short, wide, cut away past point for a single. They have managed to break the 250 barrier but they would end up on the losing side
Bhuvneshwar to Vijaykumar Vyshak, 1 run, nails the yorker, Vijaykumar Vyshak digs it down to long-on for a single. 34 off 2 balls now
Bhuvneshwar to Anuj Rawat, FOUR, fuller ball, outside off, Anuj Rawat got the room and creamed it over cover. Superb hitting

Bhuvneshwar to Anuj Rawat, FOUR, gets under it and scoops it over short fine for a four. The game ends with SRH winning this batting feast of an affair by 26 runs. This was insane. This was crazy. The adjectives will follow....

23:12 Local Time, 17:42 GMT, 23:12 IST: The boxing game has ended. The two puglists didn't punch each other. They punched helpless punching bags or should I say bowlers. In the end, SRH landed more blows than RCB. Who wants to be a bowler? 277 few nights back, 287 today. SRH are setting some stern benchmarks for T20 batting. Head had a massive tailwind to start off and scored a ton off 39 balls. Klaasen at 3 carried on like he does and Samad blasted a 10-ball 37. RCB were out-batted. Faf and Kohli came out all guns blazing. But Kohli fell and that opened the door for a collapse as Markande and Cummins ate up the top-order. Both of them were superb on a wicket which had nothing in it for the bowlers. But RCB finished with 262 as DK came up with some lusty exhibtion of big innovative hitting. He timed the ball like a dream but didn't have much support from the other end. RCB have now lost 5 on the bounce. They are languishing at the bottom of the table. And the bowling effort today would have scarred them further. Tough one indeed for the home side!

Faf du Plessis: Much better (batting performance) from us, that was a proper t20 wicket. Just tried to get close in the end, but 280 was very far. It's tough. We tried a few things, we tried different things. There's no way to hide when your confidence is low. The fast bowlers found it quite difficult out there. Similar to the batting perspective, we need to work on few areas. Need to make sure the run rate doesn't go down after powerplay. The guys put up their hand and never gave up (in the run chase). It was good to see the fight, 30-40 runs from the bowling perspective was a bit too much. It's important to go away and freshen your mind, it's such a mental game. Sometimes you feel your mind is going to explode. When you get back to the contest you have to give full commitment.

Klaasen: It was unbelievable, that was a special knock by Head, put the pressure on the bowlers. I took a bit of time, knocked the ball around, waited for the bad balls and made sure he (Head) faced majority of the balls. It's nice to have bowlers under pressure. Haven't been training a lot, but had a good session (before the match). That fine tuning worked tonight. We have been lucky, it was a good wicket, just needed to execute (our plans.) Their batters also played well (during the run chase.)

Pat Cummins: Wish I was a batter. Wonderful game of cricket. Amazing scenes. Good fun. You try your best. If you bowl an over of 7 or 8, you can have an impact on the game. I have given up trying to read the wicket. Chinnaswamy looked dry. Really happy. Four wins now. The batters have gone about it having a smile on their faces.

Travis Head, Player of the Match: Had some food, had a shower. Exciting game again after the Mumbai game. Played beautifully. We thought we had to adapt in the first six overs. But we had the batting order and they had the license to after the bowlers. We compliment each other well. He is a young guy. We fed off each other's confidence. Pleased with how I hit the ball today.

Four out of the top five totals in the history of the IPL have come in this season. Two of those happened today. The aggregate of 549 is the highest ever in a game of T20. The MCS is known to be a batting turf. But it was a dream today for the batters and few of them sleep-walked a few runs on it. The bowlers just went for a hiding as four of the RCB bowlers conceded more than 50 runs. The word hapless defined RCB's bowling effort and their position on the points table. SRH have 8 points from 6 games now. They will continue to climb up given their artillery with the bat. Our artillery is almost out of stock. We will restock them and come back tomorrow. Has been a pleasure for our team of MS Ramakrishnan, Nikhil Jadhav, Kumar Abhisekh Das and Harish to have covered a historic game!
